headline: Amazon And Google's 'OpenAI Dilemma' Sparks Debate On Wall Street After AI Cloud Deals
summary: OpenAI's role as "both a cloud customer and significant potential competitor" for Google and Amazon is sparking debate on Wall Street, analysts with BofA Securities wrote Friday.  Amazon stock was down a fraction early Friday while shares of Google parent Alphabet pushed higher.  Investors are increasingly asking about an "OpenAI dilemma" for Amazon and Google, BofA Securities analysts led by Justin Post wrote in a client note Friday.
